710668f-b.text:
11th Avenue, at the N. W. corner of W. 38th Street. The earlier view shows this site being used as an unloading station. View 2 shows the engineering shacks erected here. These are being utilized as a shaft entrance during the Lincoln Tunnel boring under the Hudson River.
February 7, 1932
August 31, 1934
P. L. Sperr
